ULLETIN SATURDAY MNUARX192T 12000000 Women at Gainful Work Chicago Jan 7 Only part of the wo men cjiKuged In industry during the war period nave lost tneir places inrough the return or men from the war and the lack of employment Miss Mary Ander son director of the womens bureau of tn United States Department of Labor reports Statements to the bureau from hun dreds of industry heads who employed only women during the war show that they have retained their female help while others state that they nave replac ed their wroen with male workers Miss Anderson baid Because of the volume of unemploy ment throughout the country today no accurate figures as to the number of wo men employed in Industries at present as compared with the war period are ob tainable I believe that when figures of the 1S20 census are available they will show more than 12000000 women in gainful occupation The census how ever will not set forth the present sit uation because unemployment has In creased by leaps and bounds since it was taken Women won the admiration of em ployers during the war period by their ability"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-01T13:34:48.669Z", "group": ["ndnp/ct", "connecticut-state-library-hartford-ct-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014086/1921-01-08/ed-1/?sp=12", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_canaan_ver01:data:sn82014086:00295866330:1921010801:0096/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=425&w=312", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_canaan_ver01:data:sn82014086:00295866330:1921010801:0096/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=851&w=625", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_canaan_ver01/data/sn82014086/00295866330/1921010801/0096.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 12, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new london", "norwich", "connecticut", "new london county", "windham county", "united states"